ğŸ“Œ Overview

This project is a Windows keylogger developed for educational and cybersecurity research purposes.
It demonstrates how keystroke capturing works at a low level, how attackers deploy payloads, and how defenders can detect such behavior.

The project also integrates with a Meterpreter session, allowing captured keystrokes to be viewed remotely.

